A second controlled explosion was carried out at a parish council chairman's house yesterday after officers called to a domestic dispute found an arsenal of weapons.

Jim Arnold, 49, was arrested last Sunday on suspicion of actual bodily harm after a report that he had attacked his wife in the quiet village of Wyverstone, Suffolk.

But when officers searched the home they allegedly found a secret hoard of deadly automatic guns, including an Uzi sub machine gun and an AK-47 assault rifle.

