A
 45-year-old woman from the Stowmarket area, who was arrested on 
suspicion of possession of a prohibited firearm, has been bailed until 
May 21.

'Everyone in the village is wondering what's going on'

Anne Hornsblow, who 
lives near Arnold's home with her husband Rob and their children, said: 
'Everyone in the village is wondering what's going on.

'There's
 a lot more talking going on and everyone seems to be taking their dogs 
for a walk outside our house to see what's been happening.'

A
 Suffolk Police spokesman said: ‘Police would like to reassure residents
 that there is no risk to the general public and that controlled 
explosions such as these are standard procedure when dealing with 
potentially dangerous items.’

